<title>USA: Alcoa sees Q3 charges, worldwide job cuts.</title>
<headline>Alcoa sees Q3 charges, worldwide job cuts.</headline>
<dateline>PITTSBURGH 1996-09-27</dateline>
<text>
<p>Alcoa said Friday it will take after-tax charges of $65.5 million, or $0.38 per common share, against its 1996 third quarter earnings.</p>
<p>A $60 million charge, or $0.34 per share, will be for permanent layoffs and to fund incentives for employees who volunteer to leave, the company said.</p>
<p>Worldwide, 2,900 employees will be affected, including about 475 salaried employees in the United States. The job cuts are to be completed by the end of 1997, the company said.  </p>
<p>The remainder of the charge, $5.5 million, will mainly cover a write-down of manufacturing equipment, the company said.</p>
